possessions.description: A statement approved by the Impostor Synod, or preached at the Church in the Wild.
possessions.availableAt: Currently, this may be acquired by visiting the phantasies of the Bohemian Sculptress in the Viric Jungle.

possessions.name: Aeolian Scream
possessions.description: Scarce A curse from the lips of a forgotten god. Music like cold-forged iron spearheads. The Bazaar will pay handsomely!
possessions.availableAt: Create this by using other Wild Words items in your inventory.

possessions.name: Correspondence Plaque
possessions.description: Scarce A lead plaque incised, carefully, with Correspondence sigils. Not too many. Apparently even lead can burn.
possessions.availableAt: Create this by using other Wild Words items in your inventory.

possessions.name: Maniac's Prayer
possessions.description: Scarce Perhaps you can distinguish ghastly truths in here? Possibly it just rhymes funny.
possessions.availableAt: Create this by using other Wild Words items in your inventory.

possessions.name: Primordial Shriek
possessions.description: Commonplace A scream sealed into a stone jar with black beeswax. Something left over from the dawn of time.

possessions.name: Night-Whisper
possessions.description: Coveted Eliminate the sound of the wind from the night, and you'll hear silence. Eliminate the silence, and you'll hear this.
possessions.availableAt: Trade Certifiable Scraps for this with the Shivering Relicker, or use a Tale of Terror!! to pursue the story of the Fidgeting Writer. Expeditions in the Forgotten Quarter also occasionally uncover them.

possessions.name: Storm-Threnody
possessions.description: Scarce A whistled tune of raging melancholia. Unforgettable, until you pass it on.
possessions.availableAt: Create this by using other Wild Words items in your inventory. Tricksters also receive them periodically. Expeditions in the Forgotten Quarter occasionally uncover them.

possessions.name: Bottle of Black Wings Absinthe
possessions.nameAndLevel: 10 x Bottle of Black Wings Absinthe
possessions.description: Another of Mr Wines' creations. Is the liquid in the bottle actually moving independently? It's hard to be sure.

possessions.name: Bottle of Broken Giant 1844
possessions.description: Commonplace Rich and dark as blood. This vintage claims to predate the Fall.
possessions.availableAt: Create this by using other Wines items in your inventory.

possessions.name: Bottle of Greyfields 1868 First Sporing
possessions.nameAndLevel: 48 x Bottle of Greyfields 1868 First Sporing
possessions.description: A vintage often reserved for the intimates and proteges of Mr Wines.

possessions.name: Bottle of Greyfields 1882
possessions.description: Commonplace One of the better years. Tangy, with an agaric aftertaste.

possessions.name: Bottle of Morelways 1872
possessions.description: Scarce "Come quickly, I am drinking the fallen stars!"
possessions.availableAt: Create this by using other Wines items in your inventory.

possessions.name: Bottle of Strangling Willow Absinthe
possessions.nameAndLevel: 136 x Bottle of Strangling Willow Absinthe
possessions.description: Commonplace Get it off! GET IT OFF!
possessions.availableAt: Create this by using other Wines items in your inventory.

possessions.name: Vial of Tears of the Bazaar
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Vial of Tears of the Bazaar
possessions.description: Coveted A tiny flask of utter sorrow. The touch of the corked flask provokes weeping. Consume it, and be fatally consumed by melancholy.
possessions.availableAt: Occasionally, this can be found in the Forgotten Quarter; you may also exchange Fourth City Airag for it on a certain Opportunity card...

possessions.name: Bottle of Greyfields 1879
possessions.description: Commonplace The mushroom wines of the Neath are an acquired taste.

possessions.name: Cellar of Wine
possessions.description: Scarce What civilised person could be without one? This is mainly used for creating advanced items - such as joining the Young Stags' Club.
possessions.availableAt: Create this by using other Wines items in your inventory, or earn them on the fourth coil of the Labyrinth of Tigers.

possessions.name: Bottle of Fourth City Airag: Year of the Tortoise
possessions.nameAndLevel: 2 x Bottle of Fourth City Airag: Year of the Tortoise
possessions.description: Coveted At last you find an obliging Khaganian who can translate the faded label: 'For the Khan of Dreams'. The liquid inside is milky and sour.
possessions.availableAt: Trade for it in the card A Presumptuous Opportunity, in London. Expeditions in the Forgotten Quarter occasionally uncover them.

possessions.name: Oneiric Pearl
possessions.description: An intrusion into the mind, lacquered over with layer upon layer of nacreous fantasy.
possessions.availableAt: Supposedly, these form in the stomachs of zailors who are afflicted with persistent zee-dreams.

possessions.name: Ambiguous Eolith
possessions.description: Rare A thinking creature made this, or the sea made this; or both.

possessions.name: Carved Ball of Stygian Ivory
possessions.nameAndLevel: 40 x Carved Ball of Stygian Ivory
possessions.description: Coveted An intricately carved ball of black zee-monster bones. Monsters chase zailors chase monsters around its circumference.

possessions.name: Deep-zee Catch
possessions.description: Commonplace It might be some sort of fish, but best not to look too closely.

possessions.name: Moon-Pearl
possessions.description: Down here, these are the only way to know what phase the moon is in.

possessions.name: Royal-Blue Feather
possessions.description: Light as a thought, and jewel-bright.

possessions.name: A Subscription to the Gazette and a Whetted Pair of Scissors
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x A Subscription to the Gazette and a Whetted Pair of Scissors
possessions.description: Now you need never be concerned about destroying your own copy. You can have your paper-with-eye-holes and read it.

possessions.name: Apian Coronet
possessions.description: Chitin and bone and nevercold brass. The twinned perfumes of wine and honey. A feverish warmth across your brow. Would you not be a worthy ruler?

possessions.name: Aria of Tranquillity
possessions.description: A melody from Dahut. Quiets turbulent minds and waters.

possessions.name: Commander's Oneironautical Helm
possessions.description: A burnished and war-scarred helm, antique in aspect and fearsome to regard. A guard against nightmares and an invitation to dreams suitable to your station.

possessions.name: Crab-Clawed Tricorne
possessions.description: Such wear and tear inspires confidence. It says: "The monsters claimed me – and I won."

possessions.name: F.F. Gebrandt's Patent Illuminating Cap
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x F.F. Gebrandt's Patent Illuminating Cap
possessions.description: A miner's cap fitted with a highly miniaturized glim-lamp. Wearing it in a dark place turns the world blue, cyan, and peligin.

possessions.name: Fecund Amber Tiara
possessions.description: It's all glowy. It smells good. It gives everyone such lovely dreams. What could go wrong?

possessions.name: Gant Bowler of Fiduciary Responsibility
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Gant Bowler of Fiduciary Responsibility
possessions.description: Exposure to noxious fumes has driven many a milliner mad. This bowler carries a whiff of solvent, and turns the mind inexorably to matters rational, fiscal and economical.

possessions.name: Honed Ushanka
possessions.description: Not one of London's more-popular fashions, but very practical – especially when lurking outside of a cold evening. Take care when removing, lest you break the skin with the ornamental stinger.

possessions.name: Iron Hat
possessions.description: You can't go wrong with an iron hat. Except that you look ridiculous. That's a problem, certainly. Also, it rusts; it punishes the innocent vertebrae of the neck; it attracts urchins who enjoy the cheery ping of a hat-bounced pebble. It is, nevertheless, proof against dart, bullet, and light glim-fall.

possessions.name: Judgemental Hat
possessions.description: This hat claims (at length) to have adorned a traveller of the High Wilderness. It is not impressed with its present resting-place; neither with the Neath in general, nor with your head specifically. However, securely positioned sur ta tête, its scorn is directed outwards. Occasionally, it tuts.

possessions.name: Mask of the Rose
possessions.description: Mysterious and alluring. A vital accessory for revels on the Feast of the Exceptional Rose.

possessions.name: Modish Bonnet
possessions.description: Very eye-catching! But is the effect quite what you hoped for?

possessions.name: Pair of Irrigo Goggles
possessions.description: An impossible colour has settled into the glass like an ink-stain into pale wood.

possessions.name: Pair of Luminous Neathglass Goggles
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Pair of Luminous Neathglass Goggles
possessions.description: Radium! What a marvellous discovery! Perhaps you'd care for a cup of radium tea?

possessions.name: Peaceable Cowl
possessions.description: You will always arrive at Irem. This voyage will not be your last.

possessions.name: Pirate Hat
possessions.description: Ridiculous, flamboyant or menacing? You be the judge.

possessions.name: Prisoner's Mask
possessions.description: For some reason they make these things out of satin. A great deal of stale beer has been spilt on it though. You wouldn't wear it to a masked ball.

possessions.name: Semiotic Monocle
possessions.description: Nonuple-hardened glim, sun-stained rostygold, the tint of the deeper inks. What savage script could be so dangerous as to require this kind of protection?

possessions.name: Sinning Jenny's Forsaken Wimple!
possessions.description: If wimples could talk...

possessions.name: Sneak-Thief's Mask
possessions.description: Gorchett & Sons: Rendering You Usefully Anonymous Since 1851.

possessions.name: Sporing Bonnet
possessions.description: Are those really mushrooms? If they are, why do they whisper so? How is it they have taken root in your hair, and in your dreams? Who is Madame Limpid?

possessions.name: The Forsaken Crown of a Grand Devil
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x The Forsaken Crown of a Grand Devil
possessions.description: The colossal, many-tined, still-smouldering cast-off of a Grand Devil of Mt Palmerston. It is far too large to wear, but its monumental extravagance speaks to its nobility.

possessions.name: Tub of Gloam-Foam
possessions.description: 'Put this on your face. Don't ask why. No! Don't let it touch your lips!'

possessions.name: Unobtrusive Bowler Hat
possessions.description: A cranial accoutrement so common that one could easily be lost in the crowd.

possessions.name: A Cured Jillyfleur Cloak
possessions.description: The flesh has been brined, rather than leathered. All the unpleasant oozy bits have  been yanked out. You now do indeed have eyes in (or at least on) your back.

possessions.name: A Pendant of Helicon Amber
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x A Pendant of Helicon Amber
possessions.description: Amber of Helicon House, provided for you to wear until you return.

possessions.name: Academic Gown
possessions.description: To achieve this distinction, you have certainly proved your Watchfulness. Black is the colour of academic respectability. It billows impressively when you run, too.

possessions.name: Bloodstained Suit
possessions.description: Grey-dyed second-hand nankeen. It's seen one too many nights at the Medusa's Head. That may even be some of your blood on there.

possessions.name: Bundle of Fourth City Rags
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Bundle of Fourth City Rags
possessions.description: This threadbare garment whispers to you in your dreams. When you wake, sometimes you remember.

possessions.name: Bundle of Glad Rags
possessions.description: Trimmed with tattered ribbons and dyed quite a courageous colour.

possessions.name: Bundle of Ragged Clothing
possessions.description: Barely enough to preserve the wearer's modesty.

possessions.name: Neddy Suit
possessions.description: 'Yer basic tatty suit, wiv deep pockets an' a little loop for yer stick...' The kind of garb that a neddy-man might wear on the business of the Masters.

possessions.name: Pickpocket's Bane
possessions.description: Needle-sharp bones line the inside of the dark cloak, settling cool and harmless against your skin. The potential pickpocket, however, would be in for an unpleasant surprise.

possessions.name: Protective Labcoat
possessions.description: Clothes to keep the vilest stains off your real clothes.

possessions.name: Ratskin Suit
possessions.description: Commonplace There are those as looks down on your 'umble ratskin. But your 'umble ratskin is hard-wearin', it's waterproof, and it's remarkable warm. And silk comes out of a worm's arse.

possessions.name: Rough Gown
possessions.description: This gown has seen hard wear... and survived it.

possessions.name: Rusty Census-Taker's Badge
possessions.description:
The badge of one employed by the Masters immediately after the Fall, to perform an inventory – of sorts – of their new holdings. The census was never undertaken again, and the workers rapidly reassigned, or fired.

This item dates to 1862: the era of our newest game, Mask of the Rose.

possessions.name: Set of Workman's Clothes
possessions.description: Rough but serviceable. As worn by the more respectable kind of labourer, and people who definitely haven't just escaped from prison.

possessions.name: Shabby Opera Cloak
possessions.description: The years and the moths haven't been kind. But this is still a garment that enhances the pose and the sweep.

possessions.name: Smock of Four Thousand Three Hundred and Eight Pockets
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Smock of Four Thousand Three Hundred and Eight Pockets
possessions.description: Each pocket contains an instrument of highly specific utility. Marvel at the Salt-Lens, at the Trip-Clock, at the Mangler-Piece.

possessions.name: Strange-Shore Parabola Suit
possessions.description: The sunset colours are shaded with irrigo and night.

possessions.name: Viric Suit
possessions.description: People who look at you always blink afterward. Perhaps the colour is that powerful. Perhaps they find themselves on the edge of a nap. They never remember there was anything odd about the sight.

possessions.name: Viscount's Bejewelled Collar
possessions.description: The bedraggled, bejewelled collar of a noble cat. Its great size and exact match of the Viscountess' own collar prove its provenance.

possessions.name: An Ornate and Hefty Gothic Cross
possessions.nameAndLevel: 2 x An Ornate and Hefty Gothic Cross
possessions.description: The mere sight of it will fend off more nervous devils, while the heft of it is an admirable deterrent to door-to-door salesmen.

possessions.name: Avid Glove
possessions.description: The Avid Glove is a marvel of surgery and tailoring! Although it can be complicated to shake hands.

possessions.name: Flawless Hand Mirror
possessions.description: Delicate coiling writing is etched into its silver frame: 'We wouldn't be here without you.' Take a moment. Look at yourself. You're magnificent.

possessions.name: Gossamer Palms
possessions.description: Made of silk harvested from Saviour's Rocks. Sticky as sin, and quiet as death.

possessions.name: Keelgraspers
possessions.description: They have been to the peligin depths from which no living thing returns. They hold tightly to the rigging, lest they sink there again.

possessions.name: Loomweavers
possessions.description: In Irem, destinies will be woven like silk.

possessions.name: 'Lucky' Claw
possessions.description: As thick as a cat's tail, long as its leg. Painlessly sharp. This bone blade has retained its lethal form, despite passing back through the mirror.

possessions.name: Mournclimber's Wraps
possessions.description: Patchworked with puzzle-damask and soft as whispers. Used by Corsairs to scale the slick stone of their stalagmite home.

possessions.name: Pair of Lenguals
possessions.description: Polythreme's finest: gloves that can taste! And speak! And salivate!

possessions.name: Pair of Magician's Gloves
possessions.description: Spotless as an untroubled heart.

possessions.name: Pugilist's Hello
possessions.description: A merry gift commemorating the festive season. Stretched leather, ruddy as a gin drinker's nose and trussed like a crackling ham. Packs a hefty wallop, to be bestowed liberally in a seasonally apposite manner.

possessions.name: Singed and Stained Work Gloves
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Singed and Stained Work Gloves
possessions.description: A memento of when London almost fell for a second time. These hardy gloves have seen their share of picking through rubble and handling dangerous materials.

possessions.name: Strangling Willow Ring
possessions.description: A tool for picking stray truths out of the air. Carved by devils from the wood of a parasitic brass tree fed on the rich sap of sacred promises.

possessions.name: Sun-Seared Silken Gloves
possessions.description: White as the beaches of Aestival, these gossamer-light adornments remember the warmth of the sun. Perfect for a foggy London season.

possessions.name: A Book of Red Murder
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x A Book of Red Murder
possessions.description: No writing is visible within. But the pages have not forgotten.

possessions.name: A Boutonnière of Fresh Carnations
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x A Boutonnière of Fresh Carnations
possessions.description: Close your eyes. Breathe deeply. It's like you never left the Surface.

possessions.name: A Faceted Decanter of Drownie Effluvia
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x A Faceted Decanter of Drownie Effluvia
possessions.description: It has, mercifully, been bottled. Apparently this fluid coats the waters above Dahut, the City of Peace. Is it tears? Song-residue?

possessions.name: A Journal of Metaphysical Conjecture
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x A Journal of Metaphysical Conjecture
possessions.description: Perhaps truths are contained herein - obscured by riddles, misconceptions and near unintelligible handwriting.

possessions.name: A Notable Absence of Scars
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x A Notable Absence of Scars
possessions.description: Yes. You're that good.

possessions.name: A Poisoned Pen
possessions.description: It drips acrid venom alarmingly. Letters written in its inks become a public health hazard when disseminated. Produces beautiful calligraphy in shades of jade.

possessions.name: A Posy of the Neath's Finest Flowers
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x A Posy of the Neath's Finest Flowers
possessions.description: Elegant. Refined. Literally intoxicating. And wonderfully expensive.

possessions.name: A Pre-Lapsarian Speaking Tube
possessions.description: AN INSTRUMENT FOR PROJECTING YOUR VOICE. INDOOR USE NOT ADVISED.

possessions.name: A WORD, BROKEN
possessions.description: WE HAVE GIVEN OUR WORD. ERGO WE HAVE NOT KEPT OUR WORD.

possessions.name: Ancient Hunting Rifle
possessions.description: Commonplace This thing is dangerous to everyone.

possessions.name: Bejewelled Cane
possessions.description: Excuse me? Could you put a cover on that? It's blinding the butler.

possessions.name: Blooded Knife
possessions.description: A weapon that murdered someone you loved. Plenty of use left in it. But was Scathewick a weapon in his turn?

possessions.name: Brass Ring
possessions.description: Scarce A mark of the wearer's allegiance to Hell. A foolish affectation among young blades in Fallen London. Although it does suggest a certain devil-may-care glamour.
possessions.availableAt: Create this by using other Infernal items in your inventory, or by using a Tale of Terror!! to pursue the story of the Fidgeting Writer.

possessions.name: Clandestine Candle
possessions.description: Even the most experienced smuggler needs light on the Stolen River. Those waters are hungry, and swallow the unwary without trace.

possessions.name: Consonant Violin
possessions.description: Said to have been played by the Consort when he first romanced the Empress at Kensington Palace.

possessions.name: Cricket Bat
possessions.description: Thoroughly knocked-in.

possessions.name: Dilmun Club Lapel Badge
possessions.description: Opens a surprising number of doors, to those few in the know.

possessions.name: M. D_____' A_____ for _______: F____ Edition
possessions.description: A guidebook for would-be zee explorers – if only a Ministry auditor hadn't savaged it with black ink. There's still useful information to glean from the included maps.

possessions.name: Iron Republic Journal
possessions.description: '...what I had to go through to create this...'

possessions.name: Leviathan-Bone Knife
possessions.description: Carved out of the leaden bones of a zee-beast. The black, dense material lends itself to exact and thoughtful cuts – in dissection or in vivisection.

possessions.name: Mutersalt
possessions.description: Tastes like clean air and crystallised ginger. Also has the interesting property of paralysing the vocal cords if you sprinkle it in your stew.

possessions.name: Myriad Keys
possessions.description: Each key's shank bears a secret. They open a hundred mysterious doors. But try carrying them without their jingling waking the dead.

possessions.name: Nodule of Warm Amber
possessions.description: Coveted An eye-sized chunk of deep amber. Disturbingly warm to the touch. But oddly hard to put down.
possessions.availableAt: Find these in certain Bundles of Oddities, or by calling in favours with Rubbery Men.  Expeditions in the Forgotten Quarter also occasionally uncover them.

possessions.name: Nuncian Pocket Watch
possessions.description: It marks time with the regular efficiency of an overworked schoolmistress, and comes with more concealed lock-picks than possessed by the finest London cat-burglars. An officer of the post is always prepared.

possessions.name: Plate of Scandalously Buttered Scones
possessions.nameAndLevel: 3 x Plate of Scandalously Buttered Scones
possessions.description: Your Aunt spent the bulk of her better years perfecting the recipe. She kept it close, but accidentally revealed it – along with an array of shocking family secrets – during a memorable and sherry-soaked visit to your lodgings. She regretted it immediately, making you swear you would always apply the jam before the cream, as God intended.

possessions.name: Poison-Tipped Umbrella
possessions.description: The modern assassin's companion. Be careful when it rains.

possessions.name: Polythreme Drinking Vessel
possessions.description: A sweetener of prospective voters when full. A chastiser of the enemy's supporters when empty.

possessions.name: Prison Shiv
possessions.description: A chisel wrapped in a rag: a prisoner's weapon.

possessions.name: Rattus Faber Rifle
possessions.description: Coveted A rat-scaled weapon! Horribly fiddly to load. But a deadly surprise at close range.

possessions.name: Relict Catapult
possessions.description: This item is a valuable artifact of ancient urchin’s wars – between the Noughts and the Crosses. Or between the Noughts & Crosses and another, forgotten urchin gang (back when the Noughts & Crosses were one gang). Opinions differ on its origin and antiquity.

possessions.name: Scrimshander Carving Knife
possessions.description: This is a proper historian's knife. Sharp enough to carve dates into Scrimshander's bone-books. Tough enough to obliterate unwanted histories.

possessions.name: Selection of Garish Fireworks
possessions.description: For open-air use only. Storage of such explosives in the foundations of any building could have disastrous and entirely unintended consequences.

possessions.name: Set of Kifers
possessions.description: Burglar's tools. Where do the underclasses get these extraordinary words?

possessions.name: Shepherd's Timepiece
possessions.description: A subtle sign of recognition for those who would return souls to their rightful owners.
possessions.availableAt: Gain this through the Trade in Souls storyline (available on the Fate page).

possessions.name: Shuttered Cake
possessions.description: This cake was prepared for the Traitor Empress on the anniversary of the Fall, but she refused even to look at it. Its filling is as light as a raincloud. Its candles burn a melancholy blue. Its icing is black as midnight, as delicate as filigree, and as fragile as a heart.

possessions.name: Sturdy Pick
possessions.description: Your aunt's name is engraved in the handle. It looks like it's been through several wars.
possessions.availableAt: Maybe you already have one of those lying around? Look in your Lodgings.

possessions.name: The Thief With Neither Face nor Name
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x The Thief With Neither Face nor Name
possessions.description: Your spate of enigmatic thefts baffled the Constables, and inspired this penny dreadful.

possessions.name: Bright-Buckled Boots
possessions.description: Cavalier boots of supple calfskin and disarmingly shiny fittings. Liberated by the Corsairs from an Admiralty Commander, they lend your footsteps the click-clack of unquestionable authority.

possessions.name: Completely Unassuming Palaeontological Accessory
possessions.description: Palaeontologists aim to unearth the dead. In the Neath, they’re also prepared to put them down.

possessions.name: Meticulously Altered Stocking
possessions.description: Something otherworldly wore this. Something, perhaps, that can see with its feet. No: that's an absurd idea.

possessions.name: Pair of Forgotten Spidersilk Slippers
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Pair of Forgotten Spidersilk Slippers
possessions.description: Hush. You were never here.

possessions.name: Pair of Masterwork Dancing Slippers
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Pair of Masterwork Dancing Slippers
possessions.description: Poise and grace.

possessions.name: Pair of Savage Hob-Nailed Boots
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Pair of Savage Hob-Nailed Boots
possessions.description: The nails strike satisfying sparks on the cobbled streets. Some will fear you. All will hear you coming.

possessions.name: Pair of Scarlet Stockings of Dubious Origin
possessions.nameAndLevel: 2 x Pair of Scarlet Stockings of Dubious Origin
possessions.description: Mr Wines provides stockings to its employees. These are not those stockings. But they are very striking.

possessions.name: Pair of Spidersilk Slippers
possessions.description: All spider eggs have most likely been removed.

possessions.name: Pair of Vakeskin Boots
possessions.description: These can't be real. If the Vake isn't mythical, it's certainly not skinnable. But they're made of something interesting: something that glistens like crocodile-skin and squeaks like linoleum.

possessions.name: Riddlefisher's Footsteps
possessions.description: You will walk towards mystery, and answers will follow in your wake.

possessions.name: Scrimshaw Sabatons
possessions.description: The bone-plate armour of a Scrivener-Knight of Remembrance, a hero of Scrimshander from ages past. The stories of her heroism are carved into the bone.

possessions.name: Venge-Rat Waders
possessions.description: It is unclear whether these are made of venge-rats or made for venge-rats – then again, they are human-sized.

possessions.name: Vigilant Chitin-Fur Boots
possessions.description: The soft lining of these boots is toasty warm. The ornamentation gleams softly, drawing the eye. But the boots couldn't possibly look back. Could they?

possessions.name: Wax-Hardened Boots
possessions.description: Encased in a thick coat of crimson tallow, these boots are robust. You need not fear cobbles nor mud nor tacks dropped by rival campaigners again.

possessions.name: Wrecking Boots
possessions.description: Favoured in the far below port of Wrack, these boots are tough as, well, old boots. They are friend of the saboteur, the wrecker and the pirate, but the enemy of the honest zailor. Such as they are.

possessions.name: Starveling Cat
possessions.description: The wretched thing follows you about and tells wicked lies! And it eats all the food in the larder.

possessions.name: A Submerged Rector
possessions.description: He speaks fervently of Low Barnet, an underwater congregation of tolling bells and crooked crosses. They tell wild stories down there, which the Rector likes to repeat. He's marvellous value at parties.

possessions.name: Albino Rat
possessions.description: Elegant as a silver screwdriver.

possessions.name: Aurochs
possessions.description:
Aurochs eat voraciously, and grow inconveniently fast. For all its size, it's surprisingly gentle, eating delicately around your hand as you feed it.

Parts of this creature may be replicable along the railway, if you have the technology.

possessions.name: Blancmange Passenger (Blemmigan Tourist)
possessions.description: This mushroom enjoys leisurely excursions. One with a sensible itinerary, and plenty of stops for cake.

possessions.name: Canny Costermonger
possessions.description: It's very easy to underestimate this one. You think she rather likes that.

possessions.name: Carnivorous Aurochs
possessions.description:
Its vast appetites demand vast portions. You endure on the good graces of your local butcher, and learn quickly never to feed it by hand.

It may be of additional use in a Parabolan Base Camp.

possessions.name: Corresponding Ocelot
possessions.description: Eye-watering sigils occasionally form in his fur. Writes impassioned letters to the press. Enjoys a belly rub.

possessions.name: Dazed Raven Advisor
possessions.description: They say ravens can be as wise as owls. This one is not. But it does occasionally say useful things. (Find the Kindness of Ravens card to learn how to upgrade your Raven Advisor.)

possessions.name: Debonair Palaeontologist
possessions.description: Their fashions and their findings are both questionable. They assemble ancient bones the way your gin-soaked aunt assembles jigsaws, banging them into place if they don't fit. They often declare 'Nothing lubricates proper palaeontology like rum.' They are excellent value at parties.

possessions.name: Devious Henchman
possessions.description: This man is a man with a plan. You didn't pick him for his good looks.

possessions.name: Disgraced Rattus Faber Bandit-Chief
possessions.description: He still limps from his last fierce duel. Best not to remind him.

possessions.name: Double-Headed Terror Bird
possessions.description: Two heads are, where Terror Birds are concerned, toothier than one.

possessions.name: Dream-dwelling Carnivorous Aurochs
possessions.description:
It's never hungry when you meet it in dream. Do not question how it sates its appetites. Do not question the deep, dark rings under your neighbour's eyes.

May be of additional use in defending a Parabolan Base-Camp.

possessions.name: Dreamy Raven Advisor
possessions.description: It claims access to secret knowledge. But it's probably just a vivid imagination. Nice turn of phrase, though. Use a Primaeval Hint in your inventory to develop your Advisor further.

possessions.name: Elongated Spindlewolf
possessions.description: Its legs give the beast a turn of speed to match any horse. Does the excessively long nose aid the wolf in smelling? Certainly, it's at your feet tripping you over the moment you even consider preparing a meal.

possessions.name: Epistemological Mapmaker
possessions.description: The map is not the territory, but a lie gesturing at truth. By this principle they chart the reaches of the real.

possessions.name: Feline Pariah
possessions.description: It has walked with exiles and tasted all the shapes of their transgressions. It will not be shamed for what it is.

possessions.name: Forty-Nine-Voiced Warbler
possessions.description: It compliments and soothes. Everywhere it goes, it reassures people that their nightmares are meaningless and their fears unfounded, that their skin is smooth and their scales glowing.

possessions.name: Fraught Research Assistant
possessions.description: Now that they've compiled those notes on the fauna of the Stolen River, they can prepare a report on knifings in Spite.

possessions.name: Grubby Urchin
possessions.description: Sly, agile, and moderately reliable.

possessions.name: Haunted Clydesdale
possessions.description: A draft horse, not suitable for riding. Very personable, although he's seen some things he cannot forget.

possessions.name: Hound of Heaven
possessions.description: Gently glowing, the serpent has a nose for devils.

possessions.name: Inculcating Kraken
possessions.description: Consider the elegant gesticulations of its tentacles. Observe the hypnotic ripples of its mantle. Don't you think the Kraken is your friend? Shouldn't it get whatever it wants? Just sign here...

possessions.name: Inquisitive Lamp-cat
possessions.description: Ever-curious and lithe as an otter. Its purr is the low bubble of a simmering kettle.

possessions.name: Iron-Toothed Terror Bird
possessions.description:
This curious bird comprehends the world through the sharpness of mouth and claw, as your shredded kettle can attest.

May be of additional use in a Parabolan Base-Camp.

possessions.name: Liquid Debutante
possessions.description: A newcomer to all things, including himself. Always he will view himself with new eyes, and to all London he will always be arriving.

possessions.name: Lucky Weasel
possessions.description: We don't mean he brings luck to you. Things just work out for this cheery little fellow.

possessions.name: Possessed Goldfish
possessions.description: A small, foolish fish, inhabited by the will of a Fingerking. Defined more by what Is Not than by what Is.

possessions.name: Prescient Automatist
possessions.description: Indecorous truths flow from hand to canvas without ever consulting the mind. Whatever governs his dazzling works, it possesses rare and scandalous insight.

possessions.name: Godzilla (Reprehensible Lizard)
possessions.description: A lizard who has seen life, and has no regrets.

possessions.name: Rodentine Panegyrist
possessions.description: A Bazaarine poet, familiar with postlapsarian Ratty verses on the subject of saints and False-Stars, sewers and Sorrow-Spiders and all of the terrible wonders in the deep recesses of the Neath.

possessions.name: Rubbery Dragon
possessions.description: Burps gouts of steam, particularly when taken by surprise. An excellent deterrent to burglars, a nightmare to negotiate on the stairs.

possessions.name: Rubbery Feline
possessions.description: Good lord! What is this abomination? Does the Duchess know?

possessions.name: Rubbery Newcomer
possessions.description: He has recently emerged. Dust clings to his shoulders; his eyes widen at passing hansom carriages. He hasn't learned to curb the more impolite of his noises.

possessions.name: Scuttering Squad
possessions.description: The Scuttering Company: a rapacious mercenary army operating out of a baronet's larder somewhere west of Watchmaker's Hill. They may loan you a squad of especially irregular troopers for a long-term contract. The cancellation clause is pretty punishing, though.

possessions.name: Seven-Throated Warbler
possessions.description: It lives wild now, but it was bred to give testimony in the courts. Concerned with evidence, motives, and explanations, whether accurate or not. Sometimes one throat contradicts another.

possessions.name: Slavering Dream-Hound
possessions.description: It followed you home from nightmares, but it's still a good dog.

possessions.name: Squirming Reprobate
possessions.description: London fears alterity; the Reprobate embraces and delights in it. Look at the sinuousness of his limbs; marvel at their number and emergence. For every horrified onlooker, a melodious gurgle from somewhere unexpected.

possessions.name: Storm-bird
possessions.description: Found in Parabola; or perhaps it would be more accurate to say that it finds you there.

possessions.name: Stormy-Eyed Scoundrel
possessions.description: He has beheld the tempest, and the tempest has beheld he.

possessions.name: Sulky Bat
possessions.description: Where are my sodding crickets?

possessions.name: Taciturn Mynah
possessions.description: This bird can talk. She simply chooses not to talk.
possessions.availableAt: Find her at a clandestine rendezvous in Watchmaker's Hill

possessions.name: Talkative Rattus Faber
possessions.description: Yes. Yes, I know. Yes! Just shut up for a moment. Let me think!

possessions.name: The Minister of Culture
possessions.description: His true title is "Lord of Inks, Curator of Quills, and Witness to All the Years of the Phoenix."

possessions.name: The Minister of Enigmas
possessions.description: Their true title is a state secret.

possessions.name: The Minister of State Affairs
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x The Minister of State Affairs
possessions.description: Her true title is "Holder of Libraries, Highest Servant to Our Subjects, and Ultimate Counsel of His Majesty, the Prince of the Smoking Shore and Duke of all the Isles, Archipelagos and Peninsulae that were once the Sovereignty of the Humbled Satraps."

possessions.name: The Minister of War
possessions.description: His true title is "Supreme General of Our Armies, Breaker of Horses, Shatterer of Serpents, and Guardian of Our Home."

possessions.name: The Pirate-Poet, Inscribed Anew
possessions.description: There is always an abundance of stories and an insufficiency of skin. The Pirate-Poet treats herself as a palimpsest, inscribing afresh on the words of the past.

possessions.name: Tomb-Lion
possessions.description: Regal and threatening. But, dear God, the smell...
possessions.availableAt: You may encounter one when exiled to the Tomb-Colonies.

possessions.name: Transfixing Squirrel
possessions.description: The eyes – all of them – watch avidly. It is difficult to look away. Which is for the best, really, at least while handling the critter – one must be exceedingly cautious around that tail.

possessions.name: Unassuming Judge
possessions.description: He is kinder than his peers. This may make him useful to you.

possessions.name: Untried Tracklayer
possessions.description: An experienced metalworker with little understanding of the ways of the Neath. Perhaps, under your wing, he'll survive.

possessions.name: Uttermost Eel
possessions.description: Each head whispers the inky, arctic secrets of the zee. If they were once separate creatures, they are not any more; the Uttermost Eel is one and none, and yearns for the emerald depths of its spawning ground.

possessions.name: Violant-Winged Bat
possessions.description: It has flown across the Unterzee and back, and to even stranger shores. You will never be rid of it.

possessions.name: Viric Lizard
possessions.description: Its skin is the shade past green. Just looking at it makes you dozy and forgetful of anything strange you may have recently seen.

possessions.name: Wary Raven Advisor
possessions.description: Be careful. Watch the exits. I mislike this place. You can improve your Advisor further by feeding it a Diary of the Dead.

possessions.name: Weasel of Social Discomfiture
possessions.description: It is a weasel possessed by a Fingerking. Its stare makes celebrated lecturers retire to the back room with dry heaves. Its smile desolates seasoned politicians.

possessions.name: Young Terror Bird
possessions.description:
Bright-eyed and fluffy tailed, this little horror almost compensates for its sofa-based diet by nuzzling up for attention in such an adorable way.

Parts of this creature may be replicable along the railway, if you have the technology.

possessions.name: The Curator
possessions.description: You will preserve.

possessions.name: A Bronze Plaque Dedicated to Your Good Self
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x A Bronze Plaque Dedicated to Your Good Self
possessions.description: One of the osteology exhibits at the Museum of Prelapsarian History has your name on it. It claims that you are a preeminent naturalist. Maybe that's even true.

possessions.name: A Hard-Earned Knack for Repair
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x A Hard-Earned Knack for Repair
possessions.description: When ruin came to London's streets, you were there – bearing brooms, bandages, and buttresses.

enhancements.qualityName: Noticed by the Queen of Air and Darkness

possessions.name: A Member of the Order of Those Who Will Not Be Caught Red-Handed
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x A Member of the Order of Those Who Will Not Be Caught Red-Handed
possessions.description: A society of libertines and players of red games. It is an occult and secret society, not to be spoken of beyond the curtained rooms in which it meets. Equip this in your Affiliation slot to add the associated Opportunity Card to your deck.

possessions.name: An Initiate into the Perfumer's Arts
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x An Initiate into the Perfumer's Arts
possessions.description: You know a little of how scent can be used to cloud the senses, alter histories, or end a life.

possessions.name: Dream-Shadow of a Curator's Vestige
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Dream-Shadow of a Curator's Vestige
possessions.description: The uncast reflection of a vast and winged thing stalks you in your dreams. Sometimes, it brings you gifts borne out of not-quite-gratitude.

possessions.name: Gang of Hoodlums
possessions.description: The enforcers, informers, thieves and general scum who work for an unseen underworld figure. Who happens to be you.

possessions.name: Honorary Membership in the London Horticultural Society
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Honorary Membership in the London Horticultural Society
possessions.description: Though the Society's renewed Horticultural Show was rudely interrupted by a city-wide catastrophe, the spirit of that heady glasshouse lives on in all who were there to witness the beauty you created.

possessions.name: Inducted into the Inverted Stalactite Society
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Inducted into the Inverted Stalactite Society
possessions.description: There is a place in the Prickfinger Wastes that waits to change you.

possessions.name: Membership of God's Editors
possessions.description: Making the good word better.

possessions.name: The Absent Sun (Newspaper)
possessions.description: Your very own organ of the press. Of course, you will bear this responsibility with grace and integrity.

possessions.name: Seven of St Eligius' Very Own Beard Hairs
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Seven of St Eligius' Very Own Beard Hairs
possessions.description: You are assured that these are not rat's whiskers; they are long, grey and stiff. Revered by rats and zailors alike, St Eligius is said to protect against glim-fall, against losing small tools, and against silver tarnish in mirrors.

possessions.name: The Final Resting Place of an Old Friend
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x The Final Resting Place of an Old Friend
possessions.description: She doesn't fly these days – but she did more than enough flying for one lifetime. Her guns don't fire. Her engine doesn't thrum. But when you speak of that day – when you point to the singes on her hull, the dents and the clawmarks – you leave people in no doubt that once, she soared.

possessions.name: The Rank of Flight Captain
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x The Rank of Flight Captain
possessions.description: You have an official commission as an officer in London's Air Fleet. Yes, those are naval epaulettes. No, you don't get a salary.

possessions.name: The Rose Giveth Its Verses to Devils and Also to You
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x The Rose Giveth Its Verses to Devils and Also to You
possessions.levelDescription: A trio of devil poets have entrusted you with the first steps of the Rose Giveth and a glimpse into hellish poetic forms
possessions.description: Rumours say that you’re known to dance with devils of poetic ambition, that your verses are immortalized in Hell's brass halls and your metaphors burn through parchment. But, of course, they're only rumours.

possessions.name: Your Name in F.F. Gebrandt's Address Book
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Your Name in F.F. Gebrandt's Address Book
possessions.description: She calls on you, sometimes – to pick your brain about the price of emeralds, the movements of the Austrian foreign office, or the fluctuating salinity of the unterzee.

possessions.name: Clay Sedan Chair
possessions.description: The chair is of oak, horsehair and velvet. Only the men carrying it, and you, are clay.

possessions.name: Conspicuously Liveried Carriage
possessions.description: It would be, of course, illegal for you to make false claims that you are a FitzClarence, or in any other way a descendant of royal bastards. But the carriage lays on the implication of such thickly.

possessions.name: Corpulent Carriage
possessions.description: A misshapen monstrosity, refashioned by the monks of Godfall. Its flank is warm to the touch, its interior plump and comfortable. After long journeys, you fancy you can hear it pant.

possessions.name: Most Humbling Expression of Her Majesty's Esteem
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Most Humbling Expression of Her Majesty's Esteem
possessions.description: The wheels move so quietly that careless passersby are in danger of stepping out into your path. The horses are so spirited that it takes the constant vigilance of an expert driver to keep them working together. But for someone relaxing inside, it is the finest ride anyone could wish for.

possessions.name: Obdurate Stallion
possessions.description: Nothing will deter him from his path. Including you, often, alas.

possessions.name: Semi-Automated Mary Lloyd
possessions.description: Is this a child's toy, or a discarded festival invention? The creature's jaw is wired in such a way that as you cycle, its mouth clacks open and closed. Guaranteed to frighten the horses.

possessions.name: Velocipede
possessions.description: "Coming through! Coming through with woefully inefficient brakes!"

possessions.name: Weeping Litter-Cyst
possessions.description: A replica of the Fathomking's own. His Complexity's is much larger, of course – but even this small reef-bier has its power.

possessions.name: An Exemplary Work of Lapsarian Theological Art
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x An Exemplary Work of Lapsarian Theological Art
possessions.description:
Found in a basement, alongside several battered copies of Hymns Ancient and Modern from which all references to the sun and moon have been blotted out.

This item can be used as well as equipped. Visit your Possessions page to make use of it.

possessions.name: Cloud-filled Sphere
possessions.description: A pale amber sphere, filled with longing. Art, unlike anything seen in London before.

possessions.name: Diatomist's Array
possessions.description: A mahogany box, varnished to a resonant shine, containing a brass array replete with a range of lavishly curated lenses. What miniature vistas await to delight your eye?

possessions.name: Formidable Basalt Gymnasium
possessions.description: Stone floor and black iron weights. Serious business.

possessions.name: Lightfingers' Folly
possessions.description: The police have been setting up suspiciously appealing homes to lure burglars. Now, canny thieves avoid any home with a cracked window and a thoughtlessly open safe. Ironically, then, such safes are becoming the perfect place in which to hide your valuables.

possessions.name: Overwrought Bathtub
possessions.description: Hissing, clanking, and often-explosive. This steaming brass marvel attempts to solve the problem of tepid bathwater – by breaking half of the laws of the universe.

possessions.name: Portable Lamp-Post
possessions.description: Complete with Farthing & Sons patented telescopic mechanism, it can be transported with ease and style, before being erected at whatever location you consider needs more flattering light.

possessions.name: Unopened Bottle of Broken Giant 1899 'Century Label'
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x Unopened Bottle of Broken Giant 1899 'Century Label'
possessions.description: A vintage of sparkling mushroom wine specifically prepared to celebrate the turning of the Century. Given the Empress' decision to have nothing to do with the 20th Century, most such bottles were drunk sadly and alone sometime in the first week of 1899 – the second 1899, that is. Remaining ones have become collector's items, and confer a certain prestige to anyone who held on to them.

possessions.name: Voluminous Library
possessions.description: Like having a thousand erudite friends. Except they don't drink your port and ask to borrow money.

possessions.name: Nyx-class Zubmersible
possessions.description: Like zailing over someone's grave. Don't ask who built her, or for what purpose. Don't ask what purpose she might have for you.

possessions.name: The Bloodied Travelling-Coat of Mr Cups
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x The Bloodied Travelling-Coat of Mr Cups
possessions.description: The coat is made for a huger frame than yours, and drags heavily behind you. It is rimed with old, eternal frost from some high wilderness, creaking and cracking with every step. The ghost of a far wind attends it, making it billow at dramatic moments. The hem is still stained dark with the blood of its previous owner.

possessions.name: A Pot of Violant Ink
possessions.nameAndLevel: 1 x A Pot of Violant Ink
possessions.description: Violant is the colour of necessary, but troublesome, connections. The ink tastes like pitch mixed with tears.
